# RESIDENTIAL LEASE AGREEMENT  
44724 Big Meadows Rd, Proctor, Montana 59929

This Residential Lease Agreement (“Agreement”) is entered into as of ____________, 2026, by and between:

- **Landlord:** Michael Kyle Chandler (“Landlord”)  
- **Tenants:** Malcom Smith and Angie Smith (collectively, “Tenant” or “Tenants”)

Landlord and Tenants are sometimes referred to individually as a “Party” and collectively as the “Parties.”

---

## 1. Premises; Use; Occupancy

1.1 **Premises.** Landlord leases to Tenants the single‑family dwelling located at **44724 Big Meadows Rd, Proctor, Montana 59929**, consisting of a 3 bedroom, 2 bath home (the “Premises”).  

1.2 **Outbuildings Excluded.** Any barn, shop, or other outbuildings on the property are **excluded** from this Lease and remain in Landlord’s sole possession and control; Tenants shall not use, enter, or store property in such structures.  

1.3 **Use.** The Premises shall be used solely as a private residence and for no business or commercial purposes, except with Landlord’s prior written consent.  

1.4 **Occupancy Limit.** Occupancy is limited to **Malcom Smith and Angie Smith and their minor children only**. Overnight guests are permitted for up to 14 cumulative days in any 6‑month period unless Landlord provides prior written consent to longer stays.  

1.5 **Compliance With Law.** Tenants shall comply with all applicable federal, state, and local laws, including the Montana Residential Landlord and Tenant Act, MCA Title 70, Chapter 24 ([table of contents](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/parts_index.html)).[web:16][web:19]  

---

## 2. Term; Renewal

2.1 **Term.** The initial fixed term (“Initial Term”) begins on **February 1, 2026** and ends on **July 31, 2026**.  

2.2 **Renewal Option.** If Tenants are not in default, this Lease may be renewed for successive **6‑month terms** upon mutual written agreement of the Parties at least 30 days before the end of the then‑current term. If the Parties do not sign a renewal but Tenants hold over with Landlord’s consent and acceptance of rent, the tenancy converts to month‑to‑month under the same terms except as modified by law, consistent with [MCA § 70‑24‑201](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/part_0020/section_0010/0700-0240-0020-0010.html).[web:1]  

2.3 **Early Termination.** Early termination rights and remedies shall be as provided by this Agreement and applicable Montana law, including [MCA § 70‑24‑201(2)(f)](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/part_0020/section_0010/0700-0240-0020-0010.html) regarding damages for early termination without cause.[web:1]  

---

## 3. Rent; Fees; Security Deposit

3.1 **Rent Amount.** Tenants shall pay Landlord monthly rent of **One Thousand Four Hundred Dollars ($1,400.00)**.  

3.2 **Due Date; Method.** Rent is due and payable **in advance on the first (1st) day of each month** without demand, at the address or account designated by Landlord, as allowed by [MCA § 70‑24‑201(2)(b)–(c)](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/part_0020/section_0010/0700-0240-0020-0010.html).[web:1] If the Initial Term begins on a date other than the 1st, the first payment may be prorated as agreed in writing.  

3.3 **Late Fees.** If rent is not received by the 5th calendar day of the month:  
- **First late month during the Lease Term:** No late fee.  
- **Second and each subsequent late month during the Lease Term:** A flat **late fee of Fifty Dollars ($50.00)** per month is assessed.  

3.4 **Returned Payments.** Tenants shall pay a fee of $________ for each returned check or failed electronic payment, plus any bank charges actually incurred.  

3.5 **Security Deposit.**  
- Amount: **One Thousand Four Hundred Dollars ($1,400.00)** (“Security Deposit”), equal to one month’s rent.  
- Landlord may withhold from the Security Deposit for unpaid rent, late fees, utilities owed under this Lease, cleaning beyond ordinary wear and tear, and damages as permitted by [MCA § 70‑25‑201](https://law.justia.com/codes/montana/title-70/chapter-25/part-2/section-70-25-201/).[web:93][web:97]  
- Landlord shall provide Tenants a written, itemized list of any deductions and refund the remaining Security Deposit within the time limits set by [MCA § 70‑25‑202](https://law.justia.com/codes/montana/title-70/chapter-25/part-2/section-70-25-202/) (within 30 days, or 10 days if no deductions).[web:93][web:97]  
- Landlord shall furnish a separate written statement of the condition of the Premises at move‑in as required by [MCA § 70‑25‑206](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0250/part_0020/section_0060/0700-0250-0020-0060.html), which Tenants shall review, note any disagreements, and sign.[web:61][web:96]  

---

## 4. Utilities and Services

4.1 **Tenant‑Paid Utilities (in Tenant’s Name).** Tenants shall arrange for and pay all charges for:  
- Electricity  
- Propane fuel (for heating and appliances)  
- Garbage/trash service  
- Telephone, cable, or upgraded internet service (if desired)  

All such accounts shall be opened in Tenants’ names as of the Commencement Date and kept current throughout the tenancy.[web:57]  

4.2 **Propane Tank.**  
- Landlord **owns and maintains** the propane tank hardware and fittings.  
- Tenants shall arrange all fuel deliveries and pay for propane consumed during the tenancy.  
- At move‑out, Tenants shall ensure the propane tank level is equal to or greater than the level documented on the move‑in condition statement or pay Landlord the value of any shortfall at prevailing rates.  

4.3 **Landlord‑Provided Services.** Landlord shall provide **limited Wi‑Fi internet access** as a courtesy service only, without guarantee as to speed, compatibility, or uptime. Tenants shall use such service lawfully and shall not hold Landlord liable for outages, security issues, or consequential damages arising from its use or unavailability.[web:62]  

4.4 **Water and Septic.**  
- The Premises are served by a **private well** and **on‑site septic system**.  
- Landlord is responsible for structural septic system maintenance and repairs (tank, drain field, major components).[web:42]  
- Tenants shall:  
  - Use water and sewer reasonably;  
  - Not dispose of grease, wipes, feminine hygiene products, diapers, cat litter, chemicals, or other non‑biodegradable materials in toilets or drains;  
  - Immediately report slow drains, backups, or sewage odors.  
- Tenants shall be liable for costs of pumping, clearing, or repairs caused by their misuse or failure to timely report issues, consistent with Montana law on tenant‑caused damages.[web:42][web:48]  

4.5 **Acceptable Use of Internet Service.**  
- Tenants shall **not** use, or permit others to use, Landlord‑provided internet service for any **illegal or unethical activity**, including but not limited to copyright infringement, hacking, unauthorized access to other systems, harassment, distribution of malware, or viewing, downloading, or distributing illegal content.  
- Tenants are solely responsible for all activity conducted via the connection in or from the Premises and shall indemnify and hold Landlord harmless from claims, investigations, or liabilities arising out of Tenants’ misuse of the service, to the extent permitted by Montana law and without waiving Landlord’s statutory duties.[web:62][web:94]  

---

## 5. Maintenance, Repairs, and Access

5.1 **Landlord Duties.** Landlord shall comply with [MCA § 70‑24‑303](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/part_0030/section_0030/0700-0240-0030-0030.html), including the duty to:  
- Maintain all electrical, plumbing, sanitary, heating, ventilating, and other facilities and appliances supplied by Landlord in good working order;  
- Keep common areas (if any) reasonably clean and safe.[web:46]  

5.2 **Tenant Duties.** Tenants shall:  
- Keep the Premises, including interior, yard areas, and exterior surfaces under Tenant’s control, in a clean and safe condition;  
- Use all facilities and appliances (including septic and well) reasonably and safely;  
- Not deliberately or negligently damage, destroy, or remove any part of the Premises;  
- Promptly notify Landlord in writing of any condition requiring repair to prevent damage or safety hazards, as reflected in Montana tenant-duty guidance.[web:40][web:43]  

5.3 **Snow Removal.** For this single‑family dwelling, Tenants agree to assume the duty to perform **basic snow and ice removal** from:  
- Driveway  
- Walkways and entry porches  

This shifting of duty is permitted by [MCA § 70‑24‑303(3)–(4)](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/part_0030/section_0030/0700-0240-0030-0030.html) when agreed to in writing for a single‑family residence.[web:46] Tenants shall perform such removal in a timely manner to reduce slip hazards.  

5.4 **Lawn and Yard Care.** Tenants shall be responsible for routine lawn mowing, trimming, and basic yard upkeep (including seasonal cleanup) to keep the Premises neat and in compliance with any applicable local standards.[web:43]  

5.5 **Entry by Landlord.**  
- Except in emergencies, Landlord shall provide at least **48 hours’ prior notice** to Tenants before entering the Premises for repairs, inspections, or showing to prospective tenants or purchasers.  
- Tenants may waive the 48‑hour requirement for specific entries by written, email, or text consent.  
- In an **emergency** (including but not limited to active water leaks, loss of essential services, fire, or conditions posing serious risk of damage or injury), Landlord may enter the Premises without prior notice as allowed by [MCA § 70‑24‑312(2)](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/part_0030/section_0120/0700-0240-0030-0120.html).[web:95][web:98]  

---

## 6. Insurance and Risk Allocation

6.1 **Landlord’s Insurance.** Landlord shall maintain property insurance on the dwelling structure. This insurance does **not** cover Tenants’ personal property or liability.[web:21][web:62]  

6.2 **Tenant’s Renter’s Liability Insurance (Required).**  
- Within **5 days** of the Commencement Date, Tenants shall obtain and maintain throughout the tenancy a renter’s liability insurance policy with minimum liability coverage of **$100,000**.  
- Tenants shall provide proof of coverage to Landlord and list Landlord as an “Interested Party” or equivalent for cancellation notices, if available from the insurer.  
- Failure to maintain required insurance is a material breach of this Lease.[web:62]  

6.3 **Personal Property at Tenant’s Risk.** Tenants’ personal property is stored on the Premises at Tenants’ sole risk. Landlord shall not be liable for loss or damage to Tenants’ personal property due to theft, fire, water, power outage, or other casualty except to the extent caused by Landlord’s willful misconduct or gross negligence and not otherwise limited by law.[web:62]  

6.4 **Indemnification by Tenants.** To the extent permitted by [MCA § 70‑24‑202](https://archive.legmt.gov/bills/mca/title_0700/chapter_0240/part_0020/section_0020/0700-0240-0020-0020.html) and other applicable law, Tenants shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Landlord from and against any claims, damages, or liabilities (including reasonable attorney fees) arising out of:  
- Tenants’ use or occupancy of the Premises;  
- Acts or omissions of Tenants, household members, guests, or invitees;  
- Violation of this Lease or applicable laws by Tenants or their guests.  

This clause does **not** waive or limit Landlord’s statutory duties or immunize Landlord from liability for Landlord’s own negligence where such waiver would be prohibited or unenforceable under Montana law.[web:94][web:31]  

---

## 7. Rules; Pets; Smoking; Illegal Activity

7.1 **Pets.** **No pets** are permitted on the Premises, whether owned, visiting, or temporary, without Landlord’s prior written consent, except as required by law for service animals or reasonable accommodations under fair housing
